Rating: 0
It is so weird when people make recipe substitutions and then report back about how horrible the recipe is. The person from Corvallis below substitutes Splenda for sugar and then complains that the texture sucks.When mixed in the correct proportions with fat and flour, sugar provides texture to cookies, and Splenda is NOT sugar. Cooks Illustrated Magazine experimented with Splenda in cookies a few years ago -- here is a link: http://www.cooksillustrated.com/taste tests/overview.asp?docid=10034 They explain in kitchen chemistry terms the reasons why cookies made with Splenda don't have the chewy texsture of those made with sugar.

