I like to try and cut down on the sugar so I altered the recipe by using 1 cup of brown sugar, and one half cup of "Fruitsource" a fruit and grain sweetener. I used one half the chocolate chips and one half a cup or raisins. They only took 8 minutes to cook and were very good. Usually the fruitsource takes away the crunchiness of the cookie, but they were soft yet chewy. Next time I will be brave enough to substitute all the sugar with the "fruitsource". It makes the sugar a more complex one, without the bad effects that refined sugar has on the system.

