Rating: 3
This recipe is really terrific! I made a few substitutions which I think now make it a superb, rich-tasting, classic chewy oatmeal raisin cookie. The substitutuions I made are: instead of light brown sugar, I used dark brown. I also added 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, left out the salt, left out the chocolate chips, left out the oat bran, and added some walnuts chopped into small pieces. I increased the raisins to about 1 1/2 cups. So, the recipe now is: 1 cup (2 sticks) of butter, room temperature 1 1/4 cups packed dark brown sugar 1/2 cup sugar 2 large eggs 1 T. vanilla extract 1 1/2 cups all purpose flour 1 t. baking soda 2 cups old-fashioned oats 1 1/2 cups raisins 1 cup walnuts, chopped into fine pieces Follow the same directions as was given in the original recipe, but I baked for eight (8) minutes only instead of 12 (but every oven is different, so it's a matter of experimentation)to get really soft (but not raw), chewy cookies, and flatted them out slightly before putting the baking sheet in the oven (they spread nicely but not too much).

